Each Target has the following properties:

**Properties**

**Description**

**Code**

Provides unique identification of the Target. All the contents produced by the user application for the Target will be placed in a directory with the same name as the Target code.

**Name**

You may assign a name to the Target without the restrictions imposed for the code.

**Description**

You may assign a description to the Target for rapid indication of its main functions.

**Spool resolution**

Indicates the resolution of the print spool produced when the Target is used. The default value is 300 DPI.

**Spool formats**

Enables spool formats for the selected Target. The default options are:

- **PDF, PDF/A **

- **AFPDS**

- **Intermediate format**

**Unprintable characters**

Allows to handle unprintable characters*:*

- **Replace with '?' **

- **Raise an error **

- **Ignore the character**

**Image resolution**

Indicates the resolution of the images produced for the spool generated with the Target. The resolution of the images is independent of the spool resolution. You can use low resolutions when the spools will be viewed on screen (e.g. 72 DPI) and high resolutions for print purposes (e.g. 300 DPI).

**Force the resolution of the external images**

Forces the resolution of external images. This option is usually not needed.

**Color images format**

Indicates the format of all color images. You can choose to use JPEG or TIFF. JPEG is recommended for a good compression-to-quality ratio.

**Monochrome images format**

Indicates the format of all black and white images. You can choose to use JPEG or TIFF. TIFF is recommended for better compression.

**JPEG**

**quality**

Indicates the quality level of all JPEG images. If an image is to be produced in JPEG the indicated quality level will be used independently of color. You can leave the quality unchanged with respect to the original but it is always recommended to choose a specific value which satisfies the requisites of the type of spool.

**When including PDF**

Select one of the available options:

- **Keep original PDF content if possible (lower size)**

- **Fit the attachment to page**: allows PDF pages that are larger than output pages to be scaled down and/or rotated so they can be fully included in the spool.

- **Always convert PDF content to image (better compatibility)**: enables the conversion of PDFs to images, even when using a spool that can support the inclusion of PDF as a native document.

## Spool formats
Setting the format tool parameters requires excellent knowledge of how Document Composition produces the spools. The product is supplied with alternative groups of settings which can be used based on necessity.

> Warning

To allow the usage of an emitter type at runtime, it must be enabled.

**Name**

**Use to...**

**PDF, PDF/A**

Produce PDFs.

**AFPDS**

Produce AFPs in black and white, minimizing spool size, or in color (only CMYK).

**Raster**

Produce Raster files, currently only TIFF images.

**PCL**

Produce PCL 5 files, black and white only.

**Postscript**

Produce PostScript files.

**Excel**

Produce Excel files.

**HTML**

Produce HTML files.

**Email**

For each input document, produce an email and a user-configurable number of documents. Requires the configuration of advanced properties.

**Pweb/Pvideo**

Produce Pweb or Pvideo.

**CSV**

Produce CSV files.

**Intermediate Format Settings**

> **Note**

The Intermediate Format emitter is always enabled

The output is an XML file, with three different split options:

- **Spool file**: Create a single XML file.

- **Shipment**: Create an XML file for each shipment.

- **Document**: Create an XML file for each document.

The XML file is a copy of the input file enriched with spool pages (compressed). The transactional data in the input file can be discarded and the images can be embedded.

The output XML file can be used as input in another DC resource that will extract the spool pages without needing to recalculate their layout.

## Spool format settings
![](data:image/png;base64,)

### **PDF and PDF/A settings**
![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Parameter**

**Description**

**PDF Standard**

Select the PDF standard to use:

- **PDF 1.4 **

- **PDFA/1-b**

**Apply device rendering to lines thinner than **

Skip the PDF instruction for borders that are thinner than a given threshold (select the desired threshold, or use the predefined value suggested by the Designer), allowing the rendering device to draw border lines at the best of its resolution.

> Note

The option is not enabled by default, allowing existing projects to avoid variation in the spool production.

**Monochrome images have transparent background**

Select this option if you want the background color of all monochrome images in the document to be transparent, allowing to expose the graphic content of the underlying layers.

> Note

If the option is not selected, the background of all monochrome images will be opaque (standard behavior).

**Fonts encoding**

Encoding fonts helps reduce the size of the PDF. With the predefined settings, the text in the PDF is encoded using a numeric index for each glyph (CID) for TrueType fonts.

The single-byte **Fonts encoding **option allows to generate PDF text strings using standard ASCII characters for the ASCII range, thus saving some space.

This option has some caveats and limitations:

- It is fully supported only by the Western Europe codepage (i.e. it is only useful when the Western Europe codepage is enabled).

- Under some conditions, it may actually increase the file size.

When using single-byte encoding, the font is completely embedded in the document, while in auto mode it is subsetted, i.e. only the characters used in the document are inserted in the output.

Generating one spool per document with this option set can decrease the size of the text, but may increase the size of the embedded fonts. The reduction is usually less than 10% of the original size, since text is already compressed in PDF documents, so the size reduction might be relevant only when generating significantly large documents.

- **Auto **

- **Single byte**

**Optimize page tree hierarchy for large documents**

The PDF standard allows the subdivision of the internal page structure in a hierarchy, to ease access to the documents. Select the checkbox **Optimize page tree hierarchy for large documents **to force the creation of a multi-level hierarchy for pages.

> Note

This option is selected by default for new projects.

**Prioritize production speed over spool size reduction**

Deselect the checkbox **Prioritize production speed over spool size reduction **to have smaller spool sizes. With the predefined setting, the PDF is produced with maximum speed, not prioritizing spool size.

> Note

This option is selected by default for new projects.

### **AFPDS settings**
![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

**Parameter**

**Description**

**Generate Form Map (FORMDEF)**

Insert a predefined FORMDEF object in the spool file.

**Force monochrome images (FS10)**

Force the color space of all images to monochrome, even when the source images are in color and the spool supports color.

**Use G4 compression on monochrome images**

Use CCITT Group 4 compression (G4) for black and white images. The images are not changed, only compressed.

**Force color to black**

Transform all colors to black.

**Allow white text in monochrome**

Enable the use of white-colored text in monochromatic mode, using the OCA color space.

**Use EBCDIC encoding**

Enable the EBCDIC encoding of text in the resulting AFP spool. If not selected, the text is encoded in ANSI.

**Color images format**

Support color images in the AFP Spool:

- JPEG

- TIFF (LZW) - uses lossless compression

The output result is the same, only the internal structure changes.

> Warning

Use only if the print shop equipment supports it.

**Chart quality**

Select the quality of chart images. A higher quality means a higher spool size. Usually the user has no need to set this option.

> Note

This setting is only applied when using JPEG color images.

**Use more resources to optimize spool**

Select this option to produce an optimized spool, lowering its size at the expense of memory and CPU. Usually the user has no need to set this option.

> Warning

Use only if the print shop equipment supports it.

**Don't use SVI in PTX**

Select this option to allow the AFP emitter to enhance the spacing of the words when the spaces to be inserted are not used to justify the text.

> Note

This option is disabled by default

> Tip

This option should only be enabled when using text fields to show tabular data aligned only with spacing. The usual and advised way to align fields is to place fields at the right position or to use a table.

### **Raster settings**
![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Parameter**

**Description**

**Rendering**

**Better image quality: **best quality of the produced image at the expense of rendering speed.

**Better rendering speed: **best speed while lowering the quality of the images.

**Compression**

Options to control the output size and compression type:

- **None: **No compression, maximum file size, but better compatibility

- **RLE: **Run-length encoding compression

- **Deflate: **Deflate compression, also known as ZIP

- **LZW: **LempelZivWelch

- **CCITT T.4(Fax G3): **Bi-level encoding, commonly used for faxes. Only for monochrome print.

- **CCITT T.6(Fax G4): **Bi-level encoding, commonly used for faxes. Only for monochrome print.

### **PCL settings**
![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Parameter**

**Description**

**Inject text into header**

Enable the injection of user-defined text into the PCL print header, before the "@ PCL ENTER" instruction. Use this option to customize the output spool header, if needed.

**Apply offset to pages**

Enable the application of an offset to page contents. Used to trim printed paper margins.

**Front**

- **Move right of (negative values move left): **Move the content of front pages horizontally by the specified amount.

- **Move down of (negative values move up): **Move the content of front pages vertically by the specified amount.

**Back**

- **Move right of (negative values move left): **Move the content of back pages horizontally by the specified amount.

- **Move down of (negative values move up): **Move the content of back pages vertically by the specified amount.

**Optional PCL command to insert in the spool header:**

An optional PCL command to be inserted in the spool header. The command must be a binary PCL 5 command. Use *\xhh *to insert a hexadecimal value (for example, use *\xAB *to insert the hexadecimal value AB).

**Increment raster character width**

Adjust the width of the characters inserted in the print spool to compensate for rounding problems when using TTF fonts with PCL.

> **Note**

The supported PCL is **PCL 5 **(generic PCL 5, HP GL/2 and PJL).

### **PostScript settings**
![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Parameter**

**Description**

**Postscript Printer Description**

Insert a printer description file to configure the spools for a specific PostScript printer. This file is known also as PPD.

**Images optimization**

Allow the configuration of image management, optimizing for speed or memory usage.

**Standard Postscript (no optimization)**: No optimization applied.

**Image caching into the printer's hard disk using PostScript forms**: Cache images on the printer using PostScript constructs. Requires a printer which supports PostScript Level 2.

**Image caching into the printer's memory**: Cache images. Requires a printer which supports PostScript 3. **Image caching into the Postscript interpreter's memory**: Cache images. Requires a printer which supports PostScript3.

> Note

The supported PostScript is PostScript Level 3.

### **Excel settings**
![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Parameter**

Description

Format

Select the Excel format:

- **Excel 93-2007 (*.xls) **

- **Excel Workbook (*.xlsx)**

**Email settings**

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

> Note

The body of the email is always the first document produced.

**Parameter**

**Description**

**Documents**

When creating an email, it is possible to generate one or more documents to be used as attachments, using a specified emitter. This table allows you to set the number and type of documents.

Add a new row for each additional document that you wish to add to the email, using the specified PDL:

- Click **Add row...**.

- Select the document format.

- (optional) Repeat to add more documents to the email

### **Intermediate Format settings**
![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Parameter**

**Description**

**Discard transactional data**

Discard the copy to the output file of input data belonging to repeatable data sections.

**Embed images**

Embed the images used in the output file. It allows to merge documents created by different DC projects, but increases the size of the output file.

Text-to-speech (TTS) is a technology which allows to convert written text to be converted to spoken words. Doxee Platform offers innovative, AI-powered TTS features in its Pvideo Designer solution.
